 A petty cash fund should be established for operating expenses of small amount;
 No cash advance should be granted to the Municipal Treasurer for implementation of infrastructure projects; and
 Trust liabilities should be remitted and paid through check directly to the respective government financial institution.

We have recommended that Management:
 secure the sanggunian approval/ resolution for the above stated expenditures implemented in CY 2017;
 submit justification why payment of the above expenditures were made despite the absence of the sangunian approval/resolution;
 henceforth, see to it that in cases of lump sum appropriations containing general terms, a separate SB appropriation ordinance/ resolution must always be secured by the Municipal Mayor to serve as an authority to enter into contract in behalf of the Municipal Government in accordance with Section 22 (c) of R.A. No. 7160 and the applicable jurisprudence.

We have recommended that the municipal mayor:
 submit justification why payment of infrastructure and other improvements amounting to ₱2,430,000.00 and ₱2,000,000.00, respectively were made despite the absence of an appropriation/s;
 henceforth, ensure the existence of an appropriation before entering into contract in behalf of the Municipal Government.

We recommend that management:
 submit immediately the lacking documents stated in Items 8.8 and 8.9 to facilitate review and evaluation;
 Henceforth, the Municipal Accountant-Designate see to it that succeeding transactions be properly supported with complete documentation and in accordance with pertinent laws, rules and regulations in order to establish the validity and propriety of the transactions and disbursements. Processing and payment of claims that are not properly documented shall be discontinued.

