We have recommended that management:
 prepare the entry to adjust the affected accounts;
 determine the actual completion date, the estimated useful life and the accumulated depreciations of the projects;
 prepare the necessary adjustments to reflect the depreciated cost of the projects; and
 furnish the audit team with updated schedules of the affected accounts.

We have recommended the following:
 Management strictly comply with the provisions of R.A. No. 10606 to promote the welfare of its officials and employees. Erring officials submit written justification/s for late/non-remittance of its withholdings due to HDMF as of year-end. Henceforth, remit all contributions and loan amortizations due to HDMF within the reglementary period to avoid imposition of sanctions, fines and penalties;
 Over-remittance made be collected from the four (4) municipal officials/employees, and fines/penalties/surcharges incurred be collected from the erring officials;
 The Municipal Accountant - Designate and the Municipal Treasurer trace back transactions to identify the municipal official and employees of prior year/s withholdings were due to properly remit the said premium contributions and loan amortizations withheld as mandated by laws, rules and regulations. Interest and surcharges for delayed remittance shall be borne by the erring officials and employees.

